</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="193D78EE35C975948492AFED55938BFB" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5E77805725C632832BE55F23DD103BFE" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47A6B44EB0A30B957BDB9F1093CAD60D" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">
Probably this species formerly (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="2D6301BEB0BC27DF320FFADE709A118A" author="Mansoorian, A" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal Public Health" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="77 - 82" refId="B40" refString="Mansoorian, A, 2000. Some freshwater snails from Northern Iran. Iranian Journal Public Health 29 (1-4): 77 - 82" title="Some freshwater snails from Northern Iran." volume="29" year="2000">Mansoorian 2000</bibRefCitation>
) was confused with 
<taxonomicName id="CBD99FECCC46BEBD6FDA9E92B7D98EB7" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tentaculata">
<emphasis id="6A5527DEDA4936222C316626DC5178DD" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">Bithynia tentaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because we had only an empty shell of this species, we do not know if it belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="671E7DA1BAAA09EDA3BF7033BCDFC562" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7D4EE3AAA76FC5FC6685675761CBE499" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="781369D665F4A82C6A26951341C84262" authorityName="Gloer &amp; Pesic" authorityYear="2006" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Pseudobithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6696E574BA49B0027BEB84DF42D6F3D7" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="18">Pseudobithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so our generic assignment is tentative. To address this question, anatomical studies of more specimens are necessary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
